


       
       urlLink Guy kawaski answers some of entrepreneurial questions here..   The most important ingredient of a good business plan is the executive summary. This should be about two pages long and answers the basic questions:   What do you do?  What pain are you solving?  Who is your team?  What is your business model?  Who is your competition?   Of this list of questions, the most important is the one about the pain you're solving. It better be real, big, and obvious to get funding.  
     

    
